WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:05.255
I found it!
I found the coupon!

00:05.255 --> 00:09.009
Okay, team, in three minutes,
this 50%‐off‐breakfast coupon

00:09.009 --> 00:11.303
becomes a 0%‐off‐
breakfast coupon,

00:11.303 --> 00:12.304
so buckle up.

00:12.304 --> 00:14.014
[ Door closes ]

00:14.014 --> 00:16.475
[ Sighs ]
What is it, Ray?

00:16.475 --> 00:18.769
Why must it always
be like this?

00:18.769 --> 00:21.730
There is no way we can make it
there in three minutes.

00:21.730 --> 00:23.482
The place is 10 minutes away.
[ Engine starts ]

00:23.482 --> 00:25.609
Is that a challenge?
No, not a challenge.

00:25.609 --> 00:27.611
I believe you can do it.
Don't show me.

00:27.611 --> 00:30.697
[ Dolly Parton's
"9 to 5" plays ]

00:33.116 --> 00:34.868
[ Tires screech ]

00:34.868 --> 00:37.204
[ Scoffs ]
10 minutes.

00:37.204 --> 00:39.414
♪ Tumble out of bed,
and I stumble to the kitchen ♪

00:39.414 --> 00:41.625
♪ Pour myself
a cup of ambition ♪

00:41.625 --> 00:43.043
♪ And yawn and stretch... ♪

00:43.043 --> 00:44.545
Yeah, construction.
Evade.

00:44.545 --> 00:46.713
[ Tires screech ]

00:46.713 --> 00:48.882
♪ Jump in the shower,
and the blood starts pumpin' ♪

00:48.882 --> 00:51.301
♪ Out on the street,
the traffic starts jumpin' ♪

00:51.301 --> 00:54.346
♪ With folks like me on the job
from 9:00 to 5:00 ♪

00:54.346 --> 00:56.306
Mmm. Hazelnut.

00:56.306 --> 00:57.683
‐Nice, right?
‐Delicious.

00:57.683 --> 01:00.060
♪ What a way to make a livin' ♪

01:00.060 --> 01:03.063
♪ Barely gettin' by ♪

01:03.063 --> 01:04.564
Not a lane!
Not a lane!

01:04.564 --> 01:05.941
Not a lane!

01:05.941 --> 01:07.192
♪ They just use your mind ♪

01:07.192 --> 01:08.986
Hey! Whoa!
What's the matter with you?!

01:08.986 --> 01:10.737
If you would put oil
in it beforehand,

01:10.737 --> 01:12.322
you wouldn't be
in the middle of the road!

01:12.322 --> 01:13.448
You better listen
to the little girl.

01:13.448 --> 01:15.117
Do you want to be
behind the van or under it?

01:15.117 --> 01:16.326
Do you want to be
under the van?

01:16.326 --> 01:17.786
♪ ...for service and devotion ♪

01:17.786 --> 01:18.829
♪ You would ‐‐ ♪

01:18.829 --> 01:19.997
[ Radar gun beeps ]

01:19.997 --> 01:20.998
[ Siren wails ]

01:20.998 --> 01:21.915
Not her.

01:21.915 --> 01:23.625
[ Wailing stops ]

01:23.625 --> 01:24.668
Life's too short.

01:24.668 --> 01:25.877
♪ 9:00 to 5:00 ♪

01:25.877 --> 01:27.379
And here we are.

01:27.379 --> 01:29.006
[ Tires screech ]

01:29.006 --> 01:32.551
♪ I swear, sometimes,
that man is out ‐‐ ♪

01:32.551 --> 01:33.844
Excuse me.

01:33.844 --> 01:36.847
There's no handicapped
placard on your car.

01:36.847 --> 01:38.557
Do you expect me to walk

01:38.557 --> 01:41.059
from all the way over there
to just...

01:45.897 --> 01:48.275
I'm sorry, love.
You were saying?

01:48.275 --> 01:49.985
Something about
difficulty walking?

01:49.985 --> 01:51.486
She got difficulty walking,
darling.

01:51.486 --> 01:52.195
Aw.

01:56.283 --> 01:57.492
Oi! Oi!

01:57.492 --> 01:58.744
Yeah, hello.

01:58.744 --> 02:00.871
Now, these ‐‐
these need a bit of a tune‐up,

02:00.871 --> 02:02.331
but he's all there upstairs,

02:02.331 --> 02:03.790
and he's got a thing
about staring.

02:05.042 --> 02:07.002
That's the finger.

02:07.002 --> 02:08.920
Work in progress.

02:16.345 --> 02:18.138
Ray: H‐E‐R‐E ‐‐

02:18.138 --> 02:21.224
"Here."
Why are we here?

02:21.224 --> 02:22.309
I don't know.

02:22.309 --> 02:23.602
Maybe she got a coupon
for a crack house.

02:23.602 --> 02:24.603
Ha!

02:24.603 --> 02:27.814
I‐T ‐‐ "It"...

02:27.814 --> 02:29.566
S‐U‐‐ "sucks."

02:29.566 --> 02:31.443
It sucks.

02:31.443 --> 02:34.071
So negative, Ray.
You haven't even seen the place.

02:34.071 --> 02:35.530
No, JJ said it.

02:35.530 --> 02:37.658
Of course you didn't,
did you, sweetheart?

02:37.658 --> 02:39.534
Bully.

02:39.534 --> 02:41.495
Now, I know you're wondering
why we're here.

02:41.495 --> 02:43.080
Well, we're moving!

02:43.080 --> 02:45.290
What? To here?

02:45.290 --> 02:46.625
Yes!

02:46.625 --> 02:48.960
Their high school just laid down
a $2 million track.

02:48.960 --> 02:51.505
I'm sorry. Moving?
Changing schools again?

02:51.505 --> 02:53.423
This will be the sixth school
in two years.

02:53.423 --> 02:55.676
We're moving because I found
the perfect situation

02:55.676 --> 02:57.219
for your brother.

02:57.219 --> 02:59.971
It is a plain old class
with a full‐time aide,

02:59.971 --> 03:01.848
someone who's gonna be
by your side,

03:01.848 --> 03:03.725
reading from your board
wherever you go ‐‐

03:03.725 --> 03:05.977
a voice.

03:05.977 --> 03:09.940
No more special ed.
Brilliant, right?

03:09.940 --> 03:11.066
But it's
crazy expensive here.

03:11.066 --> 03:14.027
Son, are you familiar
with the phrase,

03:14.027 --> 03:17.322
"Pick the worst house
in the best neighborhood"?

03:20.158 --> 03:21.284
Let's take the tour.

03:23.203 --> 03:25.038
It's right next
to the freeway.

03:25.038 --> 03:26.748
No, it's <i>close</i>
to the freeway.

03:26.748 --> 03:27.999
[ Train rumbling ]

03:29.709 --> 03:31.128
It's right next
to the train!

03:32.671 --> 03:33.922
The deck...

03:33.922 --> 03:35.507
[ Door creaks ]

03:35.507 --> 03:38.301
... was located here.

03:38.301 --> 03:40.679
So you're gonna want to avoid
the deck area.

03:40.679 --> 03:42.931
Knock on it.

03:44.099 --> 03:46.852
[ Clangs ]

03:48.895 --> 03:50.021
It's a cell tower.

03:50.021 --> 03:51.565
‐It is.
‐Yeah, it is.

03:51.565 --> 03:52.566
[ Laughs ]

03:52.566 --> 03:54.401
Like 30 bars.
I can call God.

03:58.071 --> 04:03.076
G‐I‐R‐L‐S.

04:03.076 --> 04:04.661
"Girls"?

04:04.661 --> 04:06.204
Yeah, of course an aide
will help you talk to girls.

04:06.204 --> 04:08.123
Ha!

04:08.123 --> 04:10.000
Oh. [ Laughs ]
Yeah.

04:10.000 --> 04:12.711
Hey, Ray, JJ says

04:12.711 --> 04:14.880
we should try and get
an aide for you, too.

04:14.880 --> 04:16.089
[ Both laughing ]

04:16.089 --> 04:17.382
[ Chuckles ]

04:17.382 --> 04:19.718
[ Television playing
indistinctly ]

04:21.928 --> 04:24.306
Something up?

04:24.306 --> 04:26.933
Uh, let's take a ride.

04:26.933 --> 04:28.727
We'll go watch the cars.

04:32.355 --> 04:33.607
Ray:
I don't want to move,

04:33.607 --> 04:35.609
and I can't watch Mom
get disappointed again.

04:35.609 --> 04:38.445
She thinks it's gonna fix
everything, but it won't,

04:38.445 --> 04:40.739
and we'll be on
to the next perfect place.

04:40.739 --> 04:41.990
[ Tires screech ]

04:41.990 --> 04:43.158
Oh, nice one!

04:43.158 --> 04:44.659
[ Chuckling ]
Oh, awesome!

04:44.659 --> 04:47.621
You know that.
Why don't you say anything?

04:47.621 --> 04:50.707
'Cause your mom believes,
and I love her for it.

04:50.707 --> 04:53.043
I'm not gonna take that
away from her.

04:53.043 --> 04:54.586
[ Sighs ]
Look, I get it.

04:54.586 --> 04:56.129
You're doing great
in school.

04:56.129 --> 04:58.173
You've got your friend
next door,

04:58.173 --> 05:00.050
who sucks,
by the way ‐‐ hard.

05:00.050 --> 05:01.384
That kid sucks hard.

05:01.384 --> 05:02.677
‐You're just ‐‐
‐Hold on.

05:02.677 --> 05:03.678
[ Tires screech ]

05:03.678 --> 05:05.597
And there goes
the muffler!

05:05.597 --> 05:07.808
That is glorious.

05:07.808 --> 05:10.477
[ Sighs ]
All right, how about this?

05:10.477 --> 05:13.355
We've got the old house
for a couple of weeks.

05:13.355 --> 05:16.650
I was gonna go there
and pack.

05:16.650 --> 05:18.318
What if I don't,

05:18.318 --> 05:20.862
and if the new place
doesn't work out,

05:20.862 --> 05:22.948
we just go home?

05:22.948 --> 05:25.283
Oh, my God.

05:25.283 --> 05:27.118
I get to be right,
and you get to be lazy.

05:27.118 --> 05:28.411
Those are our
favorite things.

05:28.411 --> 05:29.412
Yeah.

05:29.412 --> 05:30.413
[ Tires screech ]

05:30.413 --> 05:32.207
Oh, saw sparks on that one.
So, so cool.

05:32.207 --> 05:33.792
Everybody wants to drive around
with a fat guy.

05:33.792 --> 05:35.168
Wrong hill, pal!

05:35.168 --> 05:37.379
Okay, let's go
get JJ a voice.

05:38.880 --> 05:40.465
Gonna miss you, bro.

05:40.465 --> 05:42.884
You're leaving a lot of ass
on the table.

05:42.884 --> 05:44.553
I'm gonna miss
having someone else around

05:44.553 --> 05:45.679
who cares about astronomy.

05:45.679 --> 05:47.097
But, dude,
you're my wingman.

05:47.097 --> 05:48.515
If you're not talking me up,

05:48.515 --> 05:51.101
I'm not sure I'd get that Sophia
at that party last week.

05:51.101 --> 05:53.103
I‐I did.

05:53.103 --> 05:58.149
We were all like ‐‐
Aaahhhh.

05:58.149 --> 05:59.818
And ‐‐ And then, we ‐‐

05:59.818 --> 06:00.861
Unh!

06:00.861 --> 06:01.778
Unh.

06:01.778 --> 06:04.656
Unh. Unh. Unh.

06:04.656 --> 06:06.950
[ High‐pitched voice ]
Unh! Unh! Unh!

06:06.950 --> 06:08.910
[ Normal voice ]
Unh! Unh! Unh! Unh!

06:08.910 --> 06:11.663
JJ is so excited.

06:11.663 --> 06:15.750
He's never had an aide speak
for him before ‐‐ just mum.

06:15.750 --> 06:19.337
Suppose he is 16 now.
It's time his voice changed.

06:19.337 --> 06:20.630
[ Laughs ]

06:20.630 --> 06:24.301
Oh, yeah, no.
That means he's laughing.

06:25.635 --> 06:28.680
"Is my new voice guy cool?"

06:28.680 --> 06:30.390
Well, it's a she, and...

06:30.390 --> 06:33.393
JJ! Hello, sugar!

06:33.393 --> 06:35.353
I cannot wait to be
the ambassador

06:35.353 --> 06:36.938
for such a hip, young dude.

06:36.938 --> 06:39.858
I hit the Urban Dictionary
and got up on all the lingo.

06:39.858 --> 06:42.319
I was thinking
I'd call you J‐Tizzy.

06:43.236 --> 06:44.279
Oh, yeah,
don't do that.

06:46.909 --> 06:48.188
Maya: Look at this.

06:48.188 --> 06:50.212
Didn't I tell you
this place was gonna be great?

06:50.212 --> 06:52.003
[ School bell rings ]

06:52.003 --> 06:53.538
"Dad, I hate...

06:53.538 --> 06:55.332
this lady's voice."

06:55.332 --> 06:57.375
Yeah, son,
it's not great.

06:57.375 --> 06:59.669
Oh, the DiMeos.
Hello.

06:59.669 --> 07:02.005
I'm Dr. Miller,
your school principal,

07:02.005 --> 07:04.049
and we are so glad
that you're here

07:04.049 --> 07:06.343
just in time
for tonight's big school fair.

07:06.343 --> 07:09.179
The theme is "inclusivity."

07:09.179 --> 07:11.389
You said there
wasn't gonna be a theme.

07:11.389 --> 07:13.475
Well, you'll find
we take great pride

07:13.475 --> 07:15.769
in our progressive
and thoughtful environment.

07:15.769 --> 07:18.480
In fact, we just changed
the mascot from a Viking,

07:18.480 --> 07:20.398
with its connotation
of pillaging

07:20.398 --> 07:21.983
and male sexual
aggression,

07:21.983 --> 07:23.610
to a sea slug,

07:23.610 --> 07:27.530
which has both male
and female genitalia.

07:27.530 --> 07:28.239
Huh?

07:29.699 --> 07:32.952
Okay, then.
Let's go to school, shall we?

07:32.952 --> 07:35.288
Where's the wheelchair ramp?

07:35.288 --> 07:37.123
Right.
About that.

07:37.123 --> 07:41.086
Bye, kids!
Have a great day!

07:41.086 --> 07:42.087
A garbage ramp?

07:42.087 --> 07:43.797
It's not
just a garbage ramp.

07:43.797 --> 07:45.548
No, it's a garbage‐and‐my‐son
ramp.

07:45.548 --> 07:47.050
No, according
to the district,

07:47.050 --> 07:48.468
it's acceptable
alternate access.

07:48.468 --> 07:50.178
Oh, look,
there's someone else

07:50.178 --> 07:52.097
on the acceptable
alternate access now.

07:52.097 --> 07:56.059
What disabled luminary is on
his way to the Dumpster today?

07:56.059 --> 07:57.352
Oh, my God!

07:57.352 --> 08:00.188
It's space genius
Stephen Hawking.

08:00.188 --> 08:02.774
Enchanted, Professor.
How are you?

08:02.774 --> 08:04.526
What is this?
Is this a play?

08:04.526 --> 08:07.153
Kenneth, Mrs. DiMeo's son
uses a wheelchair.

08:07.153 --> 08:09.864
Can you assure her this is
our normal disabled egress?

08:09.864 --> 08:10.865
Sure, it is.

08:10.865 --> 08:12.325
For a ball game last week,

08:12.325 --> 08:14.119
we pushed a sweet,
crippled grandmother ‐‐

08:14.119 --> 08:16.413
"Crippled"?
Did you say "crippled"?

08:16.413 --> 08:19.040
Oh, Kenneth.
Sweet Kenneth.

08:19.040 --> 08:21.584
Okay, crash course
in basic human dignity.

08:21.584 --> 08:25.255
Let's play a little game I like
to call "Trash or Person?"

08:25.255 --> 08:26.840
I'll start you off
with an easy one.

08:26.840 --> 08:30.677
Empty bag of manure ‐‐
trash or person?

08:30.677 --> 08:31.594
Go!

08:31.594 --> 08:33.263
Um. I ‐‐

08:33.263 --> 08:34.389
It's trash!

08:34.389 --> 08:36.391
Trash.
Of course it is.

08:36.391 --> 08:38.184
Bottle ‐‐
Drunk by a person.

08:38.184 --> 08:40.103
Drunk by a person,
but it's trash.

08:40.103 --> 08:41.396
Trash or person?
Trash!

08:41.396 --> 08:42.355
Yep.

08:42.355 --> 08:43.940
[ School bell rings ]

08:43.940 --> 08:46.026
Hey. Are you new?
I'm Matt.

08:46.026 --> 08:50.947
You seem great, Matt,
but I'm just here for the day.

08:50.947 --> 08:53.950
Are you, Dr. Miller, trash?
Or are you a person?

08:53.950 --> 08:55.201
I'm a ‐‐

08:55.201 --> 08:56.661
You're a person,
Dr. Miller.

08:56.661 --> 08:57.829
Of course I am.

08:57.829 --> 08:58.663
Of course
you are a person.

08:58.663 --> 09:00.165
Oh, Doctor.

09:00.165 --> 09:02.083
Listen, here's what I think
should happen ‐‐

09:02.083 --> 09:03.835
No, I'll tell you
what's going to happen.

09:03.835 --> 09:05.378
You're gonna build a ramp
in front.

09:05.378 --> 09:07.172
Furthermore, I would like
"Crippled" here

09:07.172 --> 09:08.673
to be cited
for his language,

09:08.673 --> 09:10.592
which I think should be deemed
hate speech.

09:10.592 --> 09:11.593
Be it so deemed.

09:11.593 --> 09:15.096
Look, Miss...

09:15.096 --> 09:17.098
I enjoy
your blind‐side energy.

09:17.098 --> 09:19.142
And speaking as the black man
in Newport,

09:19.142 --> 09:20.852
a person who gets
pulled over twice

09:20.852 --> 09:22.729
before he pulls
out of the parking lot,

09:22.729 --> 09:25.815
the irony of being called
intolerant is not lost on me.

09:25.815 --> 09:28.610
Now, if you don't mind,
I have a lot of work

09:28.610 --> 09:31.237
and a little bit of
Lionel Richie to get back to.

09:31.237 --> 09:32.322
Yeah.

09:32.322 --> 09:34.824
I don't like him.

09:34.824 --> 09:36.493
Nice to meet you, Blind Side.

09:38.661 --> 09:41.456
He's here!
He's here!

09:41.456 --> 09:43.333
[ Applause ]

09:43.333 --> 09:47.087
More, come on!
Everybody stand!

09:47.087 --> 09:49.005
Oh, God.
He can't stand.

09:49.005 --> 09:51.674
The ovation is insensitive!
Everybody down.

09:51.674 --> 09:54.302
Sorry.
We're just excited.

09:54.302 --> 09:57.430
We haven't had a student
before who's ‐‐

09:58.640 --> 10:00.225
... who has ‐‐

10:02.977 --> 10:05.313
... who is taller
sitting down

10:05.313 --> 10:07.816
than any of us are
standing up.

10:07.816 --> 10:09.067
We're done with the clapping!

10:09.818 --> 10:12.070
Your classmates have something
they want to share with you.

10:12.070 --> 10:13.488
Zachary?

10:13.488 --> 10:16.282
Zachary's cousin is deaf,
so he gets it.

10:17.450 --> 10:19.410
Huh?

10:21.121 --> 10:23.665
"Why?
You don't know me."

10:23.665 --> 10:26.042
Well, we don't have to.
You're an inspiration.

10:26.042 --> 10:28.586
So, what do you say,
Mr. President?

10:28.586 --> 10:32.173
He says, "Eat a bag of ‐‐"

10:32.173 --> 10:34.175
He's flattered,
and he'll think about it!

10:37.762 --> 10:38.930
[ Stopwatch beeps ]

10:38.930 --> 10:41.015
58 seconds!
Dylan, are you kidding me?

10:41.015 --> 10:41.891
That's amazing.

10:41.891 --> 10:43.017
Thank you, Coach.

10:43.017 --> 10:44.352
72 seconds!

10:44.352 --> 10:46.229
Jackie, are you kidding me?
Amazing!

10:46.229 --> 10:47.272
Sorry, Coach.

10:47.272 --> 10:49.065
72 seconds?
That's not amazing.

10:49.065 --> 10:51.526
Yeah, it stinks,
but what we value here

10:51.526 --> 10:54.028
is doing your best,
whatever that happens to be.

10:54.028 --> 10:55.530
Oh.

10:55.530 --> 10:56.990
Why?

10:56.990 --> 10:57.907
Trust me. When ‐‐

10:57.907 --> 11:00.618
1:40.
Emma, amazing!

11:00.618 --> 11:02.620
Not amazing, Emma!

11:02.620 --> 11:04.164
You're slow!

11:04.164 --> 11:06.708
Sign my petition?
Build a wheelchair ramp?

11:06.708 --> 11:08.168
Sign my petition?

11:08.168 --> 11:10.003
Come on.
What ‐‐ What is this, now?

11:10.003 --> 11:11.171
I'm raising awareness.

11:11.171 --> 11:12.964
Of the fact
that you're nuts?

11:12.964 --> 11:15.300
Oh, word's out.
Awareness is high.

11:18.094 --> 11:21.055
You are standing
on the flowers I just planted.

11:22.891 --> 11:24.517
Oh.

11:24.517 --> 11:26.269
I don't care.

11:26.269 --> 11:27.478
[ Chuckles ]

11:27.478 --> 11:30.315
Now, you ‐‐
you're not gonna win.

11:30.315 --> 11:32.400
Hmm?
These people know who you are.

11:32.400 --> 11:35.528
They even had a big meeting
about how to handle you.

11:35.528 --> 11:37.530
Handle me?
What do you mean?
Mm‐hmm.

11:37.530 --> 11:39.699
They talked to some other school
that you went off on.

11:39.699 --> 11:40.909
Oh, what other school?

11:40.909 --> 11:41.826
‐What, Lincoln?
‐No.

11:41.826 --> 11:42.744
‐Woodbridge?
‐No.

11:42.744 --> 11:43.661
‐El Modena?
‐No.

11:43.661 --> 11:44.746
Whitman? Marshall?

11:44.746 --> 11:46.039
Fountain Valley?

11:46.039 --> 11:47.332
Does the fact
that this is taking so long

11:47.332 --> 11:48.791
tell you anything
about your patterns?

11:48.791 --> 11:51.419
Handle me, huh?
Yeah, we'll see.

11:51.419 --> 11:53.338
What can I say?
The place seems great to me.

11:53.338 --> 11:54.255
Yeah.

11:54.255 --> 11:55.173
Oi!

11:55.173 --> 11:57.342
Sea Slug, office.

12:02.764 --> 12:05.934
♪♪

12:19.572 --> 12:21.115
Jillian:
Can I help you?

12:23.076 --> 12:24.452
Oh, sorry.

12:24.452 --> 12:27.163
I was just looking
for the astronomy club.

12:27.163 --> 12:28.998
You found her.
[ Chuckles ]

12:28.998 --> 12:30.541
Care to join?

12:30.541 --> 12:32.168
Me?

12:33.753 --> 12:35.964
Okay.

12:38.883 --> 12:40.301
Jillian.

12:40.301 --> 12:42.095
Uh, thank you?

12:48.059 --> 12:51.187
♪♪

12:54.857 --> 12:56.526
So, I told that principal,

12:56.526 --> 12:59.612
"I'm not staying anywhere
that I'm not wanted ‐‐ period."

12:59.612 --> 13:01.114
Does that mean
we're done here?

13:01.114 --> 13:02.740
Nothing's official yet,
Jennifer.
Check the contract.

13:02.740 --> 13:04.117
We have you till 6:00.

13:04.117 --> 13:06.369
What do we do?
Do we go back?

13:06.369 --> 13:09.038
No, we should stay.
JJ gets an aide.

13:09.038 --> 13:10.915
I mean, we could find
someone better ‐‐

13:10.915 --> 13:12.458
maybe a guy
with a cooler voice.

13:12.458 --> 13:13.376
No offense.

13:13.376 --> 13:14.961
No, I agree.
May I go?

13:14.961 --> 13:17.630
JJ's decided I sound
like a fairy godmother.

13:17.630 --> 13:20.591
He's asked me to turn a number
of students into pumpkins.

13:20.591 --> 13:22.260
Yeah,
he hates this school.

13:22.260 --> 13:25.555
He says his class wants
to make him... president?

13:25.555 --> 13:27.682
Fine. It's not for him ‐‐
It's for me.

13:27.682 --> 13:28.850
I like the school.

13:28.850 --> 13:30.435
Why?

13:30.435 --> 13:33.104
They have a planetarium
with a girl in it who likes me.

13:33.104 --> 13:35.064
This will never
happen again.

13:35.064 --> 13:37.775
Can you guys
give it another shot?

13:37.775 --> 13:39.569
JJ, help me out.

13:39.569 --> 13:41.154
He says, "No...

13:41.154 --> 13:44.949
But my mouse friends and I can
make you a gown for the ball."

13:44.949 --> 13:45.742
Is that really necessary?

13:45.742 --> 13:47.452
Ray, come on.

13:47.452 --> 13:49.412
We can't decide to stay
just 'cause you met some girl.

13:49.412 --> 13:50.329
No, of course not.

13:50.329 --> 13:52.081
It's something I want,
so who cares?

13:52.081 --> 13:53.332
Forget what I said.

13:53.332 --> 13:54.876
Let's move.
On to the next mistake.

13:54.876 --> 13:56.502
Where are you going?
The school fair.

13:56.502 --> 13:58.004
No. They disrespected
your brother.

13:58.004 --> 13:59.797
They insulted me.
You're not going to their fair.

13:59.797 --> 14:00.923
But she asked me.

14:00.923 --> 14:02.467
Look, can you
just have my back

14:02.467 --> 14:04.177
without an argument,
just once?

14:04.177 --> 14:06.054
In which fight?
Who can keep track?

14:06.054 --> 14:07.847
All right, both of you,
calm down.

14:07.847 --> 14:09.640
I will not say
"Bibbidi‐Bobbidi‐Boo."

14:09.640 --> 14:12.268
I don't think that adds anything
to the conversation!
Yes, it does.

14:12.268 --> 14:14.270
Ray, I may find the fights,
but they start them.

14:14.270 --> 14:16.481
I'm not going to apologize
for taking care of your brother.

14:16.481 --> 14:17.398
He got the right mum.

14:17.398 --> 14:19.025
Yeah, <i>he</i> did.

14:19.025 --> 14:21.611
Really?
You ‐‐ Go upstairs.

14:21.611 --> 14:22.528
There's no upstairs here.

14:22.528 --> 14:23.529
You ‐‐
Go where your room is.

14:25.990 --> 14:27.867
[ Door closes ]

14:27.867 --> 14:29.077
I need some air.

14:40.797 --> 14:43.007
I'm right, right?
He's wrong.

14:43.007 --> 14:45.468
I'm a little wet
for this conversation.

14:51.349 --> 14:53.142
You fight and fight

14:53.142 --> 14:56.479
to make sure JJ
has a normal life.

14:56.479 --> 14:58.898
Maybe he's not the only one
who deserves that.

14:58.898 --> 15:00.399
[ Sighs ]

15:06.239 --> 15:07.573
Towel.
Maya, towel.

15:07.573 --> 15:09.450
Maya, towel.

15:09.450 --> 15:10.910
[ Train whistle blows ]

15:10.910 --> 15:12.703
Ah.
Good evening, commuters!

15:12.703 --> 15:14.622
[ Knock on door ]
Ray?

15:14.622 --> 15:16.332
Ray?

15:16.332 --> 15:20.169
Oh, listen, I know you
might want to stay here.

15:20.169 --> 15:23.714
And I know that I do
move you around a lot.

15:23.714 --> 15:25.424
Well, come on, love.

15:26.342 --> 15:27.593
[ Both scream ]

15:27.593 --> 15:28.553
Where's Raymond?!

15:28.553 --> 15:29.679
He went to the fair!

15:29.679 --> 15:31.806
This was my idea.
I need you to fire me.

15:31.806 --> 15:33.182
You are fired!
I can't take it here!

15:33.182 --> 15:35.101
You people are crazy!
You are fired!

15:35.101 --> 15:36.936
Ohh.

15:36.936 --> 15:38.437
Now, the center's gonna
send you an evaluation.

15:38.437 --> 15:40.106
Get out!

15:40.106 --> 15:42.441
♪♪

15:43.776 --> 15:45.153
[ Siren wails ]

15:45.153 --> 15:47.488
No, that's her again.
Check out the tags.

15:47.488 --> 15:50.324
They say it's not even
a vanity plate.

15:50.324 --> 15:53.327
The lady at the DMV
just gave it to her.

15:53.327 --> 15:56.205
♪♪

15:59.250 --> 16:00.751
This looks fun.

16:03.254 --> 16:05.173
Uh...

16:06.632 --> 16:09.760
Jimmy: Yep.
There's Mom's car.

16:09.760 --> 16:12.346
All right, one of you should run
with me and stop Mom.

16:12.346 --> 16:14.473
One of you should stay
with the van.

16:14.473 --> 16:17.018
Hmm. What might be
a good division of labor?

16:18.186 --> 16:19.937
Finger. Fair.

16:19.937 --> 16:21.397
[ Door opens ]

16:23.232 --> 16:24.775
You look nervous.

16:24.775 --> 16:27.195
I'm not a big heights guy.

16:27.195 --> 16:28.779
I'll keep you safe.

16:28.779 --> 16:32.325
♪♪

16:33.993 --> 16:35.119
Uh...

16:35.119 --> 16:36.370
Uh‐oh.

16:36.370 --> 16:37.455
Zane:
Jill, what the hell?

16:37.455 --> 16:38.372
Zane.

16:38.372 --> 16:39.540
Zane?

16:39.540 --> 16:41.000
There's a boyfriend?

16:41.000 --> 16:42.877
He's my friend.
Don't be mean.

16:45.713 --> 16:47.965
Up, please.

16:51.135 --> 16:54.513
Kenneth:
♪ Come on and sing my song ♪

16:54.513 --> 16:56.807
♪ All ‐‐ ♪
No! Come on!

16:56.807 --> 16:59.352
This isn't a parking space.

16:59.352 --> 17:00.937
[ Sighs ]

17:05.358 --> 17:07.818
Oh, I know
whose kid you are.

17:07.818 --> 17:09.320
What's up, man?

17:09.320 --> 17:11.906
"You sound cool."

17:13.074 --> 17:14.742
Well, of course
I sound cool.

17:14.742 --> 17:15.660
I <i>am</i> cool.

17:15.660 --> 17:19.163
"Want a job?"

17:20.248 --> 17:22.667
Are you hiring,
Blind Side Jr.?

17:22.667 --> 17:24.585
[ Screams ]

17:24.585 --> 17:26.128
Oh, it bounces, too?!

17:26.128 --> 17:28.089
Oh, no. Oh, no.

17:29.465 --> 17:30.716
Oh, no.

17:30.716 --> 17:32.552
Hello, love.

17:32.552 --> 17:34.387
[ Screams ]

17:36.305 --> 17:38.933
Try it out? Sure.

17:38.933 --> 17:42.436
"I don't want applesauce."

17:42.436 --> 17:44.355
I don't care for it
much myself.

17:44.355 --> 17:50.903
Okay, uh, "Stop leaning
on my wheelchair."

17:50.903 --> 17:54.282
What if it was more of a,
uh, "Back off, jackass"?

17:54.282 --> 17:55.324
Ah!

17:55.324 --> 17:56.701
"Do I look like
a mailbox to you?"

17:56.701 --> 17:57.994
[ Laughs ]

17:57.994 --> 18:01.163
I'm kind of liking
this act.

18:01.163 --> 18:02.290
Shall we take it
out on the road?

18:05.918 --> 18:07.753
All I wanted to do
was stay in one place

18:07.753 --> 18:08.796
for, like, a minute.

18:08.796 --> 18:10.172
[ Screams ]

18:10.172 --> 18:12.633
Oh, and you should make
all our decisions.

18:12.633 --> 18:15.261
I mean, you are the adult,
after all ‐‐ I am the child.

18:15.261 --> 18:16.887
I don't think that.

18:16.887 --> 18:18.472
You said I wasn't
allowed to get a dog.

18:18.472 --> 18:21.058
It's a big
responsibility!

18:21.058 --> 18:24.270
You don't know everything,
little boy.

18:24.270 --> 18:26.314
Do you realize,
before you ran away,

18:26.314 --> 18:29.191
I came to tell you that I gave
up on this place too soon?

18:29.191 --> 18:31.110
You were going
to apologize?

18:31.110 --> 18:34.196
Oh, must we put
a label on it?

18:34.196 --> 18:38.117
Look, yes, JJ gets
a lot of my attention.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.827
Maybe it's because
he needs me,

18:39.827 --> 18:42.830
and maybe it's because you're
so damn sure that you don't.

18:42.830 --> 18:45.249
But I hear you, Ray,
I do.

18:45.249 --> 18:46.959
And I love you.

18:46.959 --> 18:50.921
And if you don't
feel that every minute,

18:50.921 --> 18:53.215
then I'm not doing
my job properly,

18:53.215 --> 18:55.718
and for that,
I am truly, truly ‐‐

18:55.718 --> 18:58.179
[ Screams ]

18:59.764 --> 19:01.390
Again, please.

19:01.390 --> 19:02.683
Last time, kid.

19:04.769 --> 19:10.900
"Ray needs help.
We should fight them."

19:10.900 --> 19:13.069
Oh, <i>we</i> should do that?
Interesting.

19:13.069 --> 19:14.779
How many
are you gonna take on?

19:14.779 --> 19:17.990
"I have an idea."

19:17.990 --> 19:20.368
So, I think we should
give this place a shot.

19:20.368 --> 19:22.828
Great, but I think you were
about to say, "I'm sorry."

19:22.828 --> 19:25.164
Oh, I did.
You missed it.

19:25.164 --> 19:26.415
Mm.

19:26.415 --> 19:28.292
Kenneth: [ Over P. A.]
<i>Would all students</i>

19:28.292 --> 19:29.293
<i>report to the stage?</i>

19:29.293 --> 19:31.545
<i>Please report to the stage.</i>

19:31.545 --> 19:33.381
<i>Now!</i>

19:33.381 --> 19:35.091
<i>Think I'm playing</i>
<i>with y'all?!</i>

19:38.427 --> 19:41.555
<i>All right, um, the kid</i>
<i>would like to say something.</i>

19:41.555 --> 19:46.435
<i>"My name is JJ DiMeo...</i>

19:46.435 --> 19:50.773
<i>student, inspiration..."</i>

19:50.773 --> 19:52.525
[ Chuckles ]

19:52.525 --> 19:56.570
<i>"...the Wheeled Avenger,</i>
<i>the Quiet Storm,</i>

19:56.570 --> 19:58.698
<i>butt‐high lady candy."</i>

19:58.698 --> 20:01.117
[ Laughs ]

20:01.117 --> 20:02.034
Little less?

20:02.034 --> 20:03.911
Okay. Sorry.
All right.

20:03.911 --> 20:05.579
<i>"... and as of this moment,</i>

20:05.579 --> 20:08.374
<i>candidate for student council</i>
<i>president."</i>

20:08.374 --> 20:10.584
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:10.584 --> 20:13.587
[ Crowd chanting "JJ!" ]

20:13.587 --> 20:16.006
♪ Hey, don't write
yourself off yet ♪

20:16.006 --> 20:18.801
This is such
an open‐minded community!

20:18.801 --> 20:22.096
Yeah, you should see them
during Black History Month.

20:22.096 --> 20:25.474
[ Chanting continues ]

20:25.474 --> 20:28.394
♪ It just takes some time ♪

20:28.394 --> 20:30.730
♪ You're in the middle
of the ride ♪

20:30.730 --> 20:34.191
♪ Everything, everything
will be just fine ♪

20:34.191 --> 20:38.529
♪ Everything, everything
will be all right ♪

20:38.529 --> 20:40.698
♪ It just takes some time ♪

20:40.698 --> 20:43.659
♪ Little girl, you're
in the middle of the ride ♪

20:43.659 --> 20:47.163
Oh, it would seem
that you're staying.

20:47.163 --> 20:49.749
May I say
that I'm thrilled?

20:49.749 --> 20:52.668
None of these rides
have ramps.

20:57.339 --> 20:59.133
It could go bouncier.
Yeah, come on, bouncier!

20:59.133 --> 21:01.010
Or the next bouncing
she's gonna do is on your head!

21:01.010 --> 21:01.927
Yeah, what she said!

21:01.927 --> 21:02.845
Go on.
Bouncier.

21:02.845 --> 21:04.096
Whoo!

21:04.096 --> 21:06.599
It's quiet.
I'm alone.

21:06.599 --> 21:11.020
Can I do this again,
but for, like, a week?

21:11.020 --> 21:12.730
How did you get me
to do this again?

21:12.730 --> 21:15.024
Well, actually, darling,
I'm quite surprised you did.

21:15.024 --> 21:16.984
Like this, JJ?
Yeah.

21:16.984 --> 21:19.278
[ Chuckles ]
Here we go.

21:19.278 --> 21:20.529
Aah!

21:20.529 --> 21:23.157
He says, "Aah!"
